lume.help.gui_objects.title = GUI Objects
gui-object-document-tree-purpose = Document Tree: navigation of existing governed documents.
gui-object-document-tree-not = It is not a free filesystem explorer.
gui-object-document-tree-allowed = It allows selecting and referencing governed documents.
gui-object-clip-panel-purpose = Clip Panel: external intake and workflow launch.
gui-object-clip-panel-not = It is not project storage.
gui-object-clip-panel-allowed = It allows explicit intake or workflow intent.
gui-object-workspace-tabs-purpose = Workspace Tabs: container for active views.
gui-object-workspace-tabs-not = It is not a notebook, free docking system, or miniapps.
gui-object-workspace-tabs-allowed = It allows controlled views to be shown.
gui-object-readonly-viewer-purpose = Readonly Viewer: non-editable viewing with READONLY label.
gui-object-readonly-viewer-not = It is not an editor.
gui-object-readonly-viewer-allowed = It allows reading resolved content.
gui-object-chat-panel-purpose = Chat Panel: coordination, context, and structured references.
gui-object-chat-panel-not = It is not document storage or an execution engine.
gui-object-chat-panel-allowed = It allows text, references, and structured results.
gui-object-tools-panel-purpose = Tools Panel: access to controlled tools.
gui-object-tools-panel-not = It is not an autonomous orchestrator.
gui-object-tools-panel-allowed = It allows controlled Operational Tools and declarative LLM Tools.
gui-object-operational-tools-purpose = Operational Tools: controlled manual launch.
gui-object-llm-tools-purpose = LLM Tools: declarative policy, not execution in F9.5.
gui-object-knowledge-panel-purpose = Knowledge Panel: access to knowledge documents.
gui-object-knowledge-panel-not = It is not a semantic graph.
gui-object-knowledge-panel-allowed = It allows governed knowledge navigation.
gui-object-pipeline-view-purpose = Pipeline View: readonly/mock view of the F9.5 flow.
gui-object-pipeline-view-not = It does not execute AI.
gui-object-pipeline-view-allowed = It shows Document -> Chunk -> PromptSpec -> SemanticSpec -> Proposal -> Trace.
gui-object-ontology-proposal-view-purpose = Ontology Proposal View: representation of semantic proposals.
gui-object-ontology-proposal-view-not = It does not approve or persist semantics.
gui-object-ontology-proposal-view-allowed = It shows proposals as proposal, not fact.
gui-object-lume-help-purpose = Lume Help: declarative contextual help.
gui-object-lume-help-not = It is not runtime, persistent chat, active LLM, tool runner, or action approver.
gui-object-lume-help-allowed = It allows brief explanations with canonical GUI names.
